Gerald<br>
I came very close to ignoring your latest post but decided that may constitute an insult towards a fellow vet and I wouldn't want to be accuse of such a thing. It is very obvious to me that you are using my name, my posts directed at nurse ratchet as a means to send a message to Jeffery. If that is the case, fine, be my guest. However, lets be honest about it. First of all, if you read any of my posts in their entirety, it is very obvious that I take all of this very seriously. You will find no jokes in my writings.  You may find anger, hostility, grief, sadness and, even, attacks on substance of anothers writings.  But never jokes! Secondly, it is also obvious that I was being facticious in making that statement. You want to read something in it that is not there, that's your problem.  If you are upset with Jeffery, deal with it. If you want my support against Jeffery, I'll do what I can, IF, you can convince me that there is a need. In this case, I am no fool. I am intelligent enough to know that the conversations between you, Tanker, and Jeffery are out of my league. I have long ago, admitted to being no historian. I only will argue on substance of things that I know. My beef with ratchet is one of these things.<br><br>
I am truely sorry that you feel that your parents honor has been compromised. I have read every one of Jeff's posts and, while I sometime think that he can get a bit pompous and arrogant, and, possibly, an inflated ego, I find it hard to believe that he would malign your parents, intentionally or otherwise.  <br><br>
I came to this site to learn from others. I have done this and there is much more to be gained. In the process, I will find some things that will offend me to the point where I feel the need to do something about it. That is what the shit with ratchet is about. If something that Jeff has said offended you, take it up with him.  If I see that he is off the wall, I'll be there to back you or anyone else.  It has not gotten to that point yet.  You folks are debating HISTORY!  History is such a fluid subject as the &quot;facts&quot; can always be used to support suppositions on all extremes. History is not a science, it is subjective.  Expect others to have contrary views! E-mail me anytime, Gerald!
